PWOD stands for Probability of Write-off Given Default. It is a key component used in IFRS9 and Loss Given Default (LGD) calculations to estimate the likelihood that an account will reach a write-off state once it has defaulted.
PDO (Points to Double the Odds) is a project parameter used to scale and calibrate credit scorecards. It defines the number of points required to double the odds of a specific outcome, such as a default.

In scorecard development, PDO is used alongside metrics like Points at odds 16:1 to ensure success criteria for calibration are met. It is monitored across various populations, including development and holdout samples, to maintain model accuracy and stability
